    {
      "text": "Bombuzal is a puzzle video game designed by Antony Crowther (credited as \"Ratt\" in the game) and David Bishop for Image Works. The game was released in 1988 for the Amiga, Atari ST and Commodore 64. It was also released in 1989 for MS-DOS and in December 1990 in Japan for the Super Famicom, with the North American version released in August 1992 renamed as Ka-Blooey.\nThe game has a sequel/remake available for the Nintendo 64 called Charlie Blast's Territory. Among its notable features is the ability to play using either an overhead or isometric view.\nThe Super NES version of the game was later released on the Nintendo Classics service for the Nintendo Switch console in July 2021.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    }
